  "prompt": "What does job screening mean?",
  "response": "Job screening is an initial step in the recruitment process where employers evaluate candidates to determine if they meet basic qualifications for a job. This typically involves:\n\n1. Reviewing resumes and applications\n2. Checking educational and professional credentials\n3. Conducting initial phone or video interviews\n4. Verifying basic skills and experience\n5. Assessing minimum job requirements\n6. Eliminating candidates who do not meet core criteria\n\nThe goal of job screening is to narrow down the pool of applicants to a smaller group of qualified candidates who will proceed to more in-depth interviews and assessment.",
